lore.threedee.head_ancient_0.description: A helmet made of ice, cold to the touch.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_0.history: This helmet belonged to the mythical Ice King.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_0.buyer: Some private collectors have shown great interest in this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_1.history: This type of helmet was often worn by medieval knights.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_1.buyer: A museum has offered to buy this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_2.history: It's unkown how this plant is still alive.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_2.buyer: A famous botanist has shown interest in buying this specimen.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_3.description: This rock is extremely hot to the touch.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_3.history: Normally found deep inside the nether lava lakes, this rock has somehow made its way to the overworld.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_3.buyer: A mineralogist would like to buy this exemplar.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_4.history: Nobody knows who this skull belonged to.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_4.buyer: The buyer of this item wishes to remain anonymous.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_5.description: This chest contains many old, golden coins.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_5.history: It is suspected that this chest may have once belonged to a pirate.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_5.buyer: An antiques collector is willing to buy this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_6.history: This object seems to have been the central component of some larger machine.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_6.buyer: A group of scientists has offered to buy this device.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_7.history: This log suggest that this area may have hosted a jungle long times ago.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_7.buyer: A private collector wants to buy this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_8.history: This type of helmet has been worn in legendary battles.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_8.buyer: A museum has shown interest in buying this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_9.description: An interesting helmet, made of unknown materials.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_9.history: Nobody seems to know anything about this helmet.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_9.buyer: This item could be very valuable to the scientific community.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_10.descriptio: A sculpture of steve, made out of diamond.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_10.history: This item used sit inside a temple, the remains of which have never been found.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_10.buyer: This item could sell for a lot on the auction market.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_11.descriptio: A little slime that seems to have passed away long ago.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_11.history: It is not known how this poor slime came to its demise.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_11.buyer: Maybe this can still be sold somewhere.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_12.descriptio: This book is resonating some kind of strange energy.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_12.history: It seems like the book contains an ancient enchantment.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_12.buyer: The Federation of Enchantment Research would like to buy this book.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_13.descriptio: A large mouth, filled with sharp teeth.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_13.history: Luckely it seems to move very slow, so it isn't very dangerous.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_13.buyer: It is going to be diffucult to find a buyer for this entity.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_14.descriptio: A bust of a Greek soldier.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_14.history: This item seems to be rather old.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_14.buyer: A local museum is interested in this bust.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_15.descriptio: A command block, made of high quality gold.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_15.history: This item seems to have been custom made for somebody a long time ago.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_15.buyer: A redstone expert would like to buy this precious item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_16.descriptio: The head of an ancient steam golem.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_16.history: The blueprints for creating a steam golem were lost long time ago, causing the extinction of these golems.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_16.buyer: A golem expert has urged you to sell this to him.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_17.descriptio: A skull with a massive crack in it.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_17.history: This skull may belong to an ancient legendary hero, who was slain not far from where you found this skull.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_17.buyer: A historian has shown interest in this skull.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_18.descriptio: A shiny block, made of ruby.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_18.history: This must have been cut from one massive ruby.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_18.buyer: A private collector is willing to pay a great deal for this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_19.history: The origins of this pearl are unknown.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_19.buyer: A jeweler would like to buy this pearl.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_20.descriptio: A statue Notch, creator of Minecraft.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_20.history: This statue used to sit on top of an ancient shrine.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_20.buyer: A museum has offered to buy this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_21.history: It looks creepy and fills you with a sense of dread.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_21.buyer: This item may be difficult to sell.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_22.descriptio: The head of a strange creature.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_22.history: The condition of the head suggests this creature passed away not too long ago.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_22.buyer: The government is willing to pay you to hand over the head.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_23.descriptio: This type of quartz has never been seen before on this planet.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_23.history: This ball of quartz most likely arived by meteor. It is a miracle that it is still intact.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_23.buyer: A group of scientists is willing to buy this ball of quartz.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_24.history: These globes were often found in classrooms.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_24.buyer: A library would like to buy this item to put it on display.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_25.descriptio: A part of an ancient altar.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_25.history: Mulitple of these altars used to be combined to perform forbidden rituals.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_25.buyer: A collector of ancient witchcraft items is willing to buy this item for their collection.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_26.history: This type of mask comes in many varieties.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_26.buyer: A museum is willing to buy this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_27.descriptio: A small statue of a slime.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_27.history: It seems to have been carved some time ago.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_27.buyer: A local shop would like to buy this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_28.buyer: A historian wants to buy this helmet.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_29.descriptio: These blocks have been used before by many people.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_29.history: Some people that have opened these have met a terrible demise.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_29.buyer: A local gambler would like to relieve you of this object.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_30.descriptio: The head of a fallen lava knight.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_30.history: These humanoids used to be summoned by warlocks to aid them in battle.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_30.buyer: A local collector would like to purchase this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_31.descriptio: You are not supposed to know of this entity's existence.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_31.history: The creature states that you do not have the disease and that you therefore do not need his cure.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_31.buyer: A local MTF unit will meet you to re-contain the entity and has offered you money to keep quiet.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_32.descriptio: A golden statue of a cow.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_32.history: This statue used to sit inside a temple.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_32.buyer: The item could be worth a lot on the auction market.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_33.history: It is a wonder that the item is still intact.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_33.buyer: A local antiques collector would like to add this item to their collection.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_34.history: These nuggets are usually a lot smaller.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_34.buyer: A nearby smeltery will buy this nugget.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_35.history: It no longer contains any liquid.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_35.buyer: Maybe a collector of antique objects would buy this.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_36.descriptio: A small statue of a slime, made out of emerald.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_36.history: This item would likely have been sitting inside a temple.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_36.buyer: The auction market would be a great place to sell this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_37.descriptio: A mystical conduit, granting those closeby the ability to breathe underwater.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_37.history: The conduit is not supposed to run while above water, but somehow this one still seems to be active.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_37.buyer: Some scientists have shown interest in the conduit.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_38.history: Not many of these have been fabricated.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_38.buyer: Multiple collectors have placed an offer to buy this collectible.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_39.history: Some traces of organic material are present on the inside.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_39.buyer: A nearby historian would like to obtain the shell.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_40.descriptio: An idol of a mythical creature.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_40.history: It is not known how many of these exist.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_40.buyer: A local antiques collector has shown interest in this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_41.descriptio: An odd looking device, normally used to save blueprints of structures.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_41.history: It might still work, but you don't know how to use it.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_41.buyer: A construction company is willing to pay a lot for this artefact.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_42.descriptio: A cell full of radioactive radium, a by-product of spent uranium fuel cells.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_42.history: You are unsure how this ended up here.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_42.buyer: A local power plant has offered to buy the cell.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_43.descriptio: A strange artefact, filling the air with unusual energy.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_43.history: You have no clue what this artefact does.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_43.buyer: A team of researchers wants to buy the item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_44.descriptio: A cute little robot, eager to play with you.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_44.history: The robot seems to have been lost some time ago.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_44.buyer: Mei has offered you a reward for returning her friend.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_45.descriptio: A dinosaur head, somehow in good condition.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_45.history: You are unsure if this is from a real dinosaur, seeing as they're assumed to be extinct.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_45.buyer: A local scientist would like to buy the head.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_46.descriptio: A cracked rock. Some kind of purple liquid seems to flow between the cracks.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_46.history: A few of these orbs have been found before, but this is the only one with purple liquid.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_46.buyer: Many groups of scientists have shown interest in this object.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_47.descriptio: A small model of a famous horror movie creature.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_47.history: Not many of these models exist.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_47.buyer: A local collector would like to buy the model.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_48.descriptio: A box filled with old ammunition.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_48.history: The ammo might still be live, so be careful.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_48.buyer: A local collector of weaponry would like to buy the box.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_49.history: They seem to have been part of a decommissioned factory.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_49.buyer: Maybe you could sell this to a smeltery.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_50.descriptio: A cobblestone generator in a small box.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_50.history: Many factories have at least one of these.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_50.buyer: A local factory has placed a bid on the generator.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_51.descriptio: A helmet made of a very strong matereial.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_51.history: Not many of these helmets have been made.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_51.buyer: A local collector would like to buy this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_52.descriptio: A helmet that used to belong to a samurai.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_52.history: The helmet seems to be slightly damaged, suggesting that it has been used in several battles.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_52.buyer: A couple of museums would like to purchase the helmet.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_53.descriptio: This artefact seems to produce energy in an unknown way.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_53.history: The structure of the object suggest that there is no limit to how much power it can generate.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_53.buyer: Many power companies have placed bids on this item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_54.history: The design of the helmet suggests it was used by some type of soldier.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_54.buyer: Maybe there are some researchers that are interested in the helmet.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_55.history: Whoever left this here is very irresponsible.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_55.buyer: You should try to sell this to somebody that knows how to properly dispose of this.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_56.history: This was likely mounted on top of an old church.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_56.buyer: The local mayor would like to buy the bell to replace the one on top of the town hall.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_57.descriptio: A disgusting smell comes from the skeleton.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_57.history: This skeleton was slain a long time ago.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_57.buyer: You are unsure how to sell the skeleton.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_58.descriptio: This beacon has lost most of its power.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_58.history: Apparently, the nether stars powering a beacon do not last forever.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_58.buyer: Some researches are willing to buy the beacon to search for the cause of its diminished power.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_59.descriptio: Mysterious voices fill your mind, and you're having odd thoughts.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_59.history: This armor was definitely used in some kind of ritual.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_59.buyer: A local collector of occult artefacts has requested the item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_60.history: It's odd how this ended up here.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_60.buyer: A local smelterly would like to process the silver.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_61.descriptio: A mob spawner that is unable to spawn mobs due to an artificial barrier.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_61.history: Whatever this used to spawn, it must have been so powerful that the spawner couldn't be destroyed.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_61.buyer: Several researches would like to buy the spawner to find out how to replicate the barrier.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_62.descriptio: A part of an end portal.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_62.history: This suggests that there is a way to destroy portals once they're formed, since the remaining frames are still lost.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_62.buyer: Somebody has approached you, stating that they are willing to pay a great deal for the item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_63.descriptio: A health kit containing several usefull supplies.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_63.history: It seems like most of the materials inside are still useable.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_63.buyer: A local hospital is interested in the item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_64.descriptio: A nether version of the conduit.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_64.history: Nobody has ever seen such an object before, so its powers are still unknown.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_64.buyer: It seems like many people are interested in this unique object.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_65.descriptio: A strange device filled with magma.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_65.buyer: A local smeltery would like to buy the item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_66.descriptio: The object radiates with intense energy.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_66.history: This item is highly unstable and should be handled with care.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_66.buyer: A top secret laboratory has approached you with an offer.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_67.history: It is still in good condition.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_67.buyer: A private collector has placed a bit on the item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_68.descriptio: The anchor is no longer charged.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_68.history: This object will only work in the nether.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_68.buyer: A local adventurer wants to buy the anchor.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_69.history: The robot needs to be wound up in order to function.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_69.buyer: A friend would like to buy the item.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_70.descriptio: A powerful generator that consumes ender related objects to produce power.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_70.buyer: A power company has placed a bid on the generator.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_71.descriptio: A drill-bit made of one of Minecraft's strongest materials.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_71.history: This drill-bit seems to be in good condition.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_71.buyer: A nearby quary would like to buy the drill-bit.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_72.descriptio: A blueprint for some kind of small factory.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_72.history: You can't seem to find out what the factory would produce.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_72.buyer: A construction company has placed a bid on the blueprint.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_73.descriptio: These things just seem end up absolutely everywhere don't they?
lore.threedee.head_ancient_73.history: Imagine being so bad at golf that your golfball ends up encased in stone.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_73.buyer: The local golf club would like to add the golfball to their supply.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_74.descriptio: A device capable of sending redstone wirelessly.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_74.history: It seems to be still transmitting to a receiver labeled WRR-76a2.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_74.buyer: An explorer would like to buy the object.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_75.descriptio: A device capable of receiving redstone wirelessly.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_75.history: It seems to be still receiving from a sender labeled WRS-22j7.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_75.buyer: An explorer would like to buy the object.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_76.descriptio: HOW DID A NUKE END UP LOST UNDERGROUND!?? PLEASE BE CAREFUL WITH THAT!
lore.threedee.head_ancient_76.history: Well, at least it's not a Biome Buster or you'd really be in trouble.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_76.buyer: The Bomb Squad is on its way to dispose of the nuke, and is willing to give you a reward for the discovery.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_77.descriptio: One of the earliest camera models used.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_77.history: It seems to be missing the tripod its supposed to be mounted on.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_77.buyer: A museum has offered to buy the camera.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_78.history: It seems to be some sort of statue, but you are not sure.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_78.buyer: A collector of ancient artefacts would like to buy the artefact.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_79.history: It somehow survived the detonation of the payload and can be reused.
lore.threedee.head_ancient_79.buyer: A private military company would like to buy the engine.

description.threedee.mortar_and_pestle: This block will grind valid materials into other materials.
description.threedee.tiny_cauldron: This block will moisturize valid materials.
description.threedee.head_fabricator: This block will summon a random decorative head when provided with catalyst. Stronger catalysts give higher odds for rarer heads.
description.threedee.head_assembler: This block will duplicate the decorative head on top when provided with enough dye paste and the correct catalyst.
description.threedee.head_recycler: This block will recycle objects into some of their core components.
description.threedee.cat_bone_meal: This potent version of Bone Meal will instantly grow any planted crop, including catalyzed seeds!.
description.threedee.handsaw: This block will cut valid materials into other materials.
description.threedee.artefact_analyzer: This block will analyze ancient materials, revealing the artefacts they conceal.
description.threedee.cat_upgrade: Right click on a decorative head to upgrade it to a 3D model.
description.threedee.cat_upgrade_limited: Note: Not all heads have a 3D model yet.
description.threedee.cat_downgrade: Right click on a 3D model to downgrade it to a decorative head.
description.threedee.negotiator: This block will search for a buyer for an artefact.
description.threedee.artefact_exchanger: This block will exchange artefacts for tokens.
description.threedee.item_exchanger: This block will exchange tokens for items.
instruction.threedee.general.leftclick: Left click with an empty hand to toggle stackmode.
instruction.threedee.general.rightclick: Right click with a valid ingredient to craft the matching output.
instruction.threedee.head_fabricator.rig: Right click with a catalyst to add it to the fabricator.
Right click with an empty hand to see the current amount of catalyst in the fabricator.
instruction.threedee.head_fabricator.lim: The fabricator can only hold one type of catalyst at a time.
instruction.threedee.head_fabricator.lef: Shift left click to change the speed of the fabricator.
instruction.threedee.head_fabricator.bro: Drops its held catalyst when broken.
instruction.threedee.head_assembler.righ: Right click with Dye Paste to add it to the assembler.
Right click with an empty hand to see the current amount of Dye Paste in the assembler.
instruction.threedee.head_assembler.head: Place a decorative head on top of the assembler.
instruction.threedee.head_assembler.righ: Right click with the matching catalyst to duplicate the head on top.
instruction.threedee.head_assembler.brok: Drops its held dye paste when broken.
instruction.threedee.head_recycler.right: Right click with an item to add it to the recycler. If the item is already present in the machine, then it is added to the queue for that item.
instruction.threedee.head_recycler.order: The recycler will always recycle the items in the order they were inserted until the queue for the first item is empty.
instruction.threedee.head_recycler.right: Right click an empty hand to see the remaining items inside.
instruction.threedee.head_recycler.limit: The recycler can only hold MARKER1 different items at once.
instruction.threedee.head_recycler.broke: WARNING: Breaking the recycler will corrupt all items inside, yielding less valuable outputs.
instruction.threedee.artefact_analyzer.r: Right click with an item to add it to the analyzer.
instruction.threedee.artefact_analyzer.l: The analyzer can only analyze one object at a time.
instruction.threedee.artefact_analyzer.b: WARNING: Due to the fragile nature of ancient materials, breaking the machine will destroy the object inside.
instruction.threedee.negotiator.rightcli: Right click with an item to add it to the negotiator.
instruction.threedee.negotiator.limit: The negotiator can only hold one artefact at a time.
instruction.threedee.negotiator.broken: Breaking the negotiator will return the artefact inside.
instruction.threedee.exchangers.rightcli: Right click with an emty hand to view the token balance of the token card inside.
instruction.threedee.exchangers.shift_ri: Shift right click with an emty hand to retrieve the token card from the machine.
instruction.threedee.exchangers.rightcli: Right click with a token card to insert it into the machine.
instruction.threedee.exchangers.broken: Breaking the machine will return the token card inside.
Right click with an artefact to convert it into tokens.
instruction.threedee.item_exchanger.righ: Right click with an item to initiate a transaction.
instruction.threedee.item_exchanger.toke: In order to make a transaction, the token card inside must have a sufficient balance.
instruction.threedee.item_exchanger.cons: Note that some transactions may consume the item you used to initiate the transaction.
_MISC_NOTE0: Some of the lines contain the word 'MARKER' with a number.
_MISC_NOTE1: DO NOT REMOVE THESE. They are used by the mod to fill in unknown values.
misc.threedee.artefact_decorative: This is a decorative replica of an orginal artefact, and therefore it cannot be sold.
misc.threedee.artefact_price: This artefact is worth between MARKER1 and MARKER2 tokens.
misc.threedee.artefact_offer: The negotiated price for this artefact is MARKER1 tokens.
misc.threedee.artefact_saleable: This item can be sold for tokens.
misc.threedee.creative_card: This card has an infinite balance.
misc.threedee.exchangers_corrupt: If you see this message, then something went wrong with the exchanger you interacted with. It may be corrupt, please break and replace it.
